d found over the years and sent it to the F.B.I.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He said he had seen the appeal of conservative antigovernment philosophies like Mr. Shea’s grow around his part of the world; people who had not been part of fringe movements in the past started to show up for meetings and embrace his messages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Shea did not respond to a request for an interview but has insisted he visited the instigators of the occupation only as a fact-finder, not as an organizer. Ammon Bundy, the Nevada rancher who led the Malheur occupation, also disputed that Mr. Shea played a role in organizing the event.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Shea called the state investigation a “coup” in a message to supporters. “The outcome of this report, like the President’s impeachment, was pre-ordained,” Mr. Shea&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mattsheawa/posts/10220880032456754\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">posted to Facebook on Saturday</a>. “What they cannot not control is our response as Patriots &amp; Christians.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a dinner gathering of far-right Christians in a remote corner of Washington State in June 2018, Mr. Shea and the online radio personality John Jacob Schmidt, whose real name is Jack Robertson, talked directly about a looming confrontation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Robertson is a prominent voice in the “<a href=\"https://radiofreeredoubt.com/\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">American Redoubt</a>” movement, which seeks to establish the inland Northwest as a place for religious conservatives to live with like-minded people.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the meeting, captured in an audio recording, they both described a divided country and warned about the dangers of left-wing agitators. Mr. Shea told the group that “liberty must be kept by force.” Mr. Robertson told attendees that he saw signs of a coming civil war and insisted that those in the room should have an AR-15 and a thousand rounds of ammunition ready.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Defend for when the bad guy comes, right?” Mr. Robertson said, as the crowd gave affirmative feedback. “Are you ready for that? But the bad guy is already here. How many of you have pulled your trigger on your AR-15 in the fight we are in yet? Not one. But there is a fight. Right now. The war is here. The bad guy is here.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2019/12/23/us/23SHEA-1509/merlin_150752130_43f0b2d7-a0ca-4fe5-92e4-c17fbbc6c889-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" alt=\"Mr. Shea giving a speech in front of the flag for Liberty, a proposed 51st state made up of conservative counties east of the Cascades.\"/><figcaption>Mr. Shea giving a speech in front of the flag for Liberty, a proposed 51st state made up of&nbsp;conservative counties east of the Cascades.Credit...Ted S. Warren/Associated Press</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"link-18d2caa\">‘No Saving You’</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shortly after Mr. Shea was elected in 2008, he began to slide toward more extremist ideologies than those he campaigned on, first aligning himself with fringe portions of the Tea Party movement and later going on to embrace conspiracy theories about the federal government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sheriff Knezovich said he approached Mr. Shea and tried to counsel him away from adopting increasingly antigovernment sentiments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“My message was: ‘Matt, if you get involved in this stuff and get that label, there will be no saving you,’” the sheriff said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But Mr. Shea became an increasingly important figure in those circles, regularly networking with activists and political leaders.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2014, Mr. Shea co-founded the Coalition of Western States, a group of conservative state lawmakers, sheriffs and others formed to counter what its advocates said was a “war on rural America” waged by an overreaching federal government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More recently, Mr. Shea has advanced a political campaign to cleave Washington State in half, hoping to create a 51st state in the conservative counties east of the Cascades.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He found additional partners in groups such as Oath Keepers, which has claimed tens of thousands of members among current and former police officers and veterans around the country. The Southern Poverty Law Center has described the organization as “one of the largest radical antigovernment groups in the U.S. today.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 2015, Mr. Shea and the leader of Oath Keepers, Stewart Rhodes — who has been public about his concern over the growing divisions in the country — met as part of a larger group at a Spokane-area restaurant. After Mr. Trump used his Twitter account in recent months to suggest that his impeachment might trigger a civil war, the Oath Keepers posted on Twitter that the president’s reference to a civil war was “the truth.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“This is where we are,”&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Oathkeepers/status/1178549790847590400\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the group wrote</a>. “We ARE on the verge of a HOT civil war. Like in 1859.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"link-2f47969a\">‘This Is Not What Liberty Is’</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Shea and his network have been readying for such a clash, though he has insisted that they have been discussing preparations to respond, not instigate. He has admitted preparing the “Biblical Basis for War” document but said it was a summary of church sermons on Old Testament war that could help place current events in historical context.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jay Pounder, a former supporter and helper of Mr. Shea, said that in the summer of 2016, he was among about 30 of Mr. Shea’s closest allies who gathered in the Spokane area to discuss plans for how they would respond to what they believed was a coming civil war.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He said they discussed possible catalysts for such a conflict — immigration, economics, left-wing antifa protests. They planned which of the members would take control of geographical regions of the Northwest, Mr. Pounder said, and chose Mr. Shea to be the eventual leader of their overall government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Pounder provided The New York Times with a variety of planning documents shared at the 2016 meeting laying out what actions should be taken in the event of a “collapse event” and describing a detailed structure of a makeshift government they would create.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The documents called for setting up sheriff’s posses, community kitchens, a “militia-based military” and communications carried out by ham radio operators. The planners called for “constitutional changes” to “sanctify to Jesus Christ” in the new government.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Pounder said the group also gathered military manuals on how to operate various weapons, such as an AT4 antitank weapon.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Pounder said he spent two years as a close ally of Mr. Shea but pulled away when he became convinced that Mr. Shea was not just a Christian conservative but was hoping to install a Christian government in the wake of civil strife that he almost seemed to welcome.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Among the other things that alarmed Mr. Pounder were conversations over encrypted messages,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/apr/20/matt-shea-rightwing-messages-chat-records#maincontent\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">made public this year</a>&nbsp;by The Guardian, in which some participants who were close allies of Mr. Shea talked about violent attacks on political opponents.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the end, he took much of what he had learned working with Mr. Shea to the F.B.I.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“I’m deeplysorry for moving this stuff along,” Mr. Pounder said. “I thought I was doing God’s will by being involved and helping Matt. This is not Christianity. This is not what liberty is.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"link-1b23ddbf\">‘To Support Armed Insurrections’</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The efforts by Mr. Pounder and Sheriff Knezovich to expose Mr. Shea ultimately led leaders in the Legislature to request an investigation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the report released last week, investigators found that Mr. Shea engaged in intimidation tactics against a political opponent as well as counterintelligence gathering. Much of the report focused on his role at the Malheur standoff, concluding that he had helped plan the event. It found that Mr. Shea “participated in an act of domestic terrorism.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The report, prepared by a company led by a former F.B.I. agent, said investigators found that Mr. Shea went to both Malheur and an earlier standoff with federal authorities in Nevada “specifically to support armed insurrections at both locations in furtherance of his Patriot Movement agenda.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2019/12/23/us/23SHEA-bundy/merlin_103143277_3a0f9c7a-46a0-43d1-a12a-47ee7c666d55-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;disable=upscale\" alt=\"Ammon Bundy at the Malheur National Wildlife Refuge in Princeton, Ore., in 2016. He said last week that Mr. Shea did not help plan the takeover there.\"/><figcaption>Ammon Bundy at the Malheur National Wildlife Refuge in Princeton, Ore., in 2016. He said last week that Mr. Shea did not help plan the takeover there.Credit...Jarod Opperman for The New York Times</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr. Bundy, one of the leaders in the Malheur standoff, disputed the findings of the report, saying in a text message on Saturday that Mr. Shea played no role in the planning of the takeover even though he supported the reasons for it. Mr. Bundy and others involved in the armed Malheur dispute&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/28/us/bundy-brothers-acquitted-in-takeover-of-oregon-wildlife-refuge.html\">were acquitted</a>&nbsp;in 2016 of federal conspiracy and weapons charges related to the event challenging the federal government’s control and management of public lands.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In response to the report, J.T. Wilcox, the leader of Republicans in the State House, said Mr. Shea had been suspended from any role in the caucus. He also urged Mr. Shea to resign.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','G.O.P. Lawmaker Had Visions of a Christian Alternative Government','','inherit','closed','closed','','83-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:33:51','2019-12-24 05:33:51','',83,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=86',0,'revision','',0),(87,1,'2019-12-24 05:40:14','2019-12-24 05:40:14','<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-caroline-flack-lewis-burton_4874499.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223101856\" alt=\"Caroline Flack was escorted into court by police\"/><figcaption>Image:Caroline Flack was escorted into court by police</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She appeared at Highbury Corner Magistrates\' Court wearing a black coat, scarf and boots and was escorted into court by police.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burton had arrived at court earlier, wearing a navy parka with a fur hood lining.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack is charged with assaulting the former professional tennis player and model at her flat in Islington, north London, on 12 December.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-lewis-burton-caroline-flack-boyfriend_4874470.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223095336\" alt=\"Lewis Burton arrives at Highbury Corner Magistrates&#39; Court, where his girlfriend Caroline Flack is charged with assault\"/><figcaption>Image:Lewis Burton arrived at the court before Caroline</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She stood in front of the glass-enclosed dock to confirm her name, address, date of birth and that her nationality is British before the single charge was read out in court.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-caroline-flack-lewis-burton_4874510.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223103352\" alt=\"The TV presenter was mobbed by photographers\"/><figcaption>Image:The TV presenter was arrested and charged on 13 December</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack wiped her eyes as she sat down in front of a full public gallery, which included Mr Burton.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She answered \"not guilty\" when the charge was put to her.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prosecutor Ms Weiss discussed the contents of the three to four-minute 999 call that Mr Burton made, saying: \"He made an allegation regarding his girlfriend Caroline.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The first police officer arrived some eight minutes later. He knocked on the door and it was opened by both of them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Both were covered in blood and in fact one of the police officers likened the scene to a horror movie\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack was released on conditional bail before her trial on 4 March, which is expected to last a day-and-a-half.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She stepped down as host of the upcoming winter series of Love Island following her arrest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-laura-whitmore-love-island_4869892.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191218140542\" alt=\"Laura Whitmore\"/><figcaption>Image:Laura Whitmore will replace Caroline Flack as presenter for the latest series of Love Island</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Irish TV presenter Laura Whitmore will replace her on the ITV2 dating show and the companion programme Aftersun when filming begins in South Africa next month.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an emotional Instagram post on Sunday evening, Ms Flack wrote: \"This is the worst time of my life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I don\'t know where to go to. Where to look. Who to trust. Or who I even am\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Caroline Flack denies attacking boyfriend with lamp','','publish','open','open','','caroline-flack-denies-attacking-boyfriend-with-lamp','','','2019-12-24 05:40:14','2019-12-24 05:40:14','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=87',0,'post','',0),(88,1,'2019-12-24 05:35:44','2019-12-24 05:35:44','','skynews-caroline-flack-leaves-court_4874688','','inherit','open','closed','','skynews-caroline-flack-leaves-court_4874688','','','2019-12-24 05:35:44','2019-12-24 05:35:44','',87,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/skynews-caroline-flack-leaves-court_4874688.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(89,1,'2019-12-24 05:40:14','2019-12-24 05:40:14','<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-caroline-flack-lewis-burton_4874499.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223101856\" alt=\"Caroline Flack was escorted into court by police\"/><figcaption>Image:Caroline Flack was escorted into court by police</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She appeared at Highbury Corner Magistrates\' Court wearing a black coat, scarf and boots and was escorted into court by police.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burton had arrived at court earlier, wearing a navy parka with a fur hood lining.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack is charged with assaulting the former professional tennis player and model at her flat in Islington, north London, on 12 December.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-lewis-burton-caroline-flack-boyfriend_4874470.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223095336\" alt=\"Lewis Burton arrives at Highbury Corner Magistrates&#39; Court, where his girlfriend Caroline Flack is charged with assault\"/><figcaption>Image:Lewis Burton arrived at the court before Caroline</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She stood in front of the glass-enclosed dock to confirm her name, address, date of birth and that her nationality is British before the single charge was read out in court.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-caroline-flack-lewis-burton_4874510.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191223103352\" alt=\"The TV presenter was mobbed by photographers\"/><figcaption>Image:The TV presenter was arrested and charged on 13 December</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack wiped her eyes as she sat down in front of a full public gallery, which included Mr Burton.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She answered \"not guilty\" when the charge was put to her.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prosecutor Ms Weiss discussed the contents of the three to four-minute 999 call that Mr Burton made, saying: \"He made an allegation regarding his girlfriend Caroline.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"The first police officer arrived some eight minutes later. He knocked on the door and it was opened by both of them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Both were covered in blood and in fact one of the police officers likened the scene to a horror movie\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Flack was released on conditional bail before her trial on 4 March, which is expected to last a day-and-a-half.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She stepped down as host of the upcoming winter series of Love Island following her arrest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-laura-whitmore-love-island_4869892.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191218140542\" alt=\"Laura Whitmore\"/><figcaption>Image:Laura Whitmore will replace Caroline Flack as presenter for the latest series of Love Island</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Irish TV presenter Laura Whitmore will replace her on the ITV2 dating show and the companion programme Aftersun when filming begins in South Africa next month.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an emotional Instagram post on Sunday evening, Ms Flack wrote: \"This is the worst time of my life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I don\'t know where to go to. Where to look. Who to trust. Or who I even am\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Caroline Flack denies attacking boyfriend with lamp','','inherit','closed','closed','','87-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:40:14','2019-12-24 05:40:14','',87,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=89',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2019-12-24 05:43:40','2019-12-24 05:43:40','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Ed Sheeran has released a new music video which shows him showering his wife, Cherry Seaborn, with kisses and appears to confirm their wedding date.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His latest video Put It All On Me, featuring singer Ella Mai, tells the different love stories of couples from all over the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ZL5SobsjnU\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ZL5SobsjnU\n</div><figcaption>Ed Sheeran reveals date of secret wedding in video featuring wife</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As they joke around, words describing their romance run along the screen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Back in high school, Ed &amp; Cherry were crushing hard,\" the message says.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They made out at the castle on the hill.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"A few years ago they reconnected, there were fireworks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They married in January 2019.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sheeran has usually remained private about his relationship with Cherry, a childhood friend who he attended school with in Suffolk.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In January 2018 he announced they were engaged, writing on Instagram: \"Got myself a fiancée just before new year. We are very happy and in love, and our cats are chuffed as well x.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In July this year he confirmed they had become husband and wife, but did not share further details.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ed Sheeran reveals date of secret wedding in video featuring wife','','publish','open','open','','ed-sheeran-reveals-date-of-secret-wedding-in-video-featuring-wife','','','2019-12-24 05:43:40','2019-12-24 05:43:40','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=90',0,'post','',4),(91,1,'2019-12-24 05:41:42','2019-12-24 05:41:42','','skynews-ed-sheeran-wife-cherry_4874452','','inherit','open','closed','','skynews-ed-sheeran-wife-cherry_4874452','','','2019-12-24 05:41:42','2019-12-24 05:41:42','',90,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/skynews-ed-sheeran-wife-cherry_4874452.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(92,1,'2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','','skynews-georgia-toffolo-toff_4873743','','inherit','open','closed','','skynews-georgia-toffolo-toff_4873743','','','2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','',90,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/skynews-georgia-toffolo-toff_4873743.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(93,1,'2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','','skynews-tony-britton-fern-actor_4873476','','inherit','open','closed','','skynews-tony-britton-fern-actor_4873476','','','2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','',90,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/skynews-tony-britton-fern-actor_4873476.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(94,1,'2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','','skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870815','','inherit','open','closed','','skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870815','','','2019-12-24 05:41:43','2019-12-24 05:41:43','',90,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870815.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(95,1,'2019-12-24 05:43:40','2019-12-24 05:43:40','<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Ed Sheeran has released a new music video which shows him showering his wife, Cherry Seaborn, with kisses and appears to confirm their wedding date.</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His latest video Put It All On Me, featuring singer Ella Mai, tells the different love stories of couples from all over the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ZL5SobsjnU\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ZL5SobsjnU\n</div><figcaption>Ed Sheeran reveals date of secret wedding in video featuring wife</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As they joke around, words describing their romance run along the screen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Back in high school, Ed &amp; Cherry were crushing hard,\" the message says.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They made out at the castle on the hill.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"A few years ago they reconnected, there were fireworks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"They married in January 2019.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sheeran has usually remained private about his relationship with Cherry, a childhood friend who he attended school with in Suffolk.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In January 2018 he announced they were engaged, writing on Instagram: \"Got myself a fiancée just before new year. We are very happy and in love, and our cats are chuffed as well x.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In July this year he confirmed they had become husband and wife, but did not share further details.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Ed Sheeran reveals date of secret wedding in video featuring wife','','inherit','closed','closed','','90-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:43:40','2019-12-24 05:43:40','',90,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=95',0,'revision','',0),(96,1,'2019-12-24 05:46:06','2019-12-24 05:46:06','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The I\'m A Celebrity winner said immigration officials were not allowing her to travel due to a damaged passport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Reality star Georgia Toffolo has said, after being released from an airport \"detention centre\" in the Maldives, she feared spending Christmas in prison.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The former I\'m A Celebrity winner had posted a series of tearful videos on Instagram to alert her followers to her plight, saying immigration officials were not allowing her to travel due to a damaged passport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She said two pages had fallen out and it meant she was not able to leave the airport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She was reportedly on her way to a luxury beach resort for a Christmas break.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-georgia-toffolo-toff_4873749.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191222154338\" alt=\"Toffolo will be able to come back to the UK for Christmas\"/><figcaption>Toffolo will be able to come back to the UK for Christmas</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In one of the videos, added to her Instagram Stories, she said officials were not allowing her to pass through immigration but would not allow her to board a flight home either.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She claimed she faced a four-day wait in a \"detention centre\" because of the issue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But after \"crying for nine hours and scaring everyone at the airport\", the 25-year-old Made In Chelsea favourite later announced she had been released and was able to move on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Georgia Toffolo released after \'facing Christmas in Maldives detention centre\'','','publish','open','open','','georgia-toffolo-released-after-facing-christmas-in-maldives-detention-centre','','','2019-12-24 05:46:37','2019-12-24 05:46:37','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=96',0,'post','',0),(97,1,'2019-12-24 05:46:06','2019-12-24 05:46:06','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The I\'m A Celebrity winner said immigration officials were not allowing her to travel due to a damaged passport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Reality star Georgia Toffolo has said, after being released from an airport \"detention centre\" in the Maldives, she feared spending Christmas in prison.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The former I\'m A Celebrity winner had posted a series of tearful videos on Instagram to alert her followers to her plight, saying immigration officials were not allowing her to travel due to a damaged passport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She said two pages had fallen out and it meant she was not able to leave the airport.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She was reportedly on her way to a luxury beach resort for a Christmas break.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-georgia-toffolo-toff_4873749.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191222154338\" alt=\"Toffolo will be able to come back to the UK for Christmas\"/><figcaption>Toffolo will be able to come back to the UK for Christmas</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In one of the videos, added to her Instagram Stories, she said officials were not allowing her to pass through immigration but would not allow her to board a flight home either.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She claimed she faced a four-day wait in a \"detention centre\" because of the issue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But after \"crying for nine hours and scaring everyone at the airport\", the 25-year-old Made In Chelsea favourite later announced she had been released and was able to move on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Georgia Toffolo released after \'facing Christmas in Maldives detention centre\'','','inherit','closed','closed','','96-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:46:06','2019-12-24 05:46:06','',96,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=97',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2019-12-24 05:47:32','2019-12-24 05:47:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A familiar face of classic British sitcoms, such as Robin\'s Nest, his film credits included The Day Of The Jackal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Don\'t Wait Up star Tony Britton has died aged 95, his TV presenter daughter Fern has announced.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Writing on Twitter, she hailed her father as a \"great actor, director and charmer\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Britton was best known for starring alongside Nigel Havers and Dinah Sheridan in the BBC sitcom Don\'t Wait Up between 1983 to 1990.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He also appeared in Thames Television\'s Robin\'s Nest, which aired from 1977 to 1981, together with Richard O\'Sullivan and Tessa Wyatt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His film credits included The Day Of The Jackal, Operation Amsterdam and Sunday Bloody Sunday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-tony-britton-dinah_4873512.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191222113324\" alt=\"Love is rekindled between Dr Toby Latimer (actor Tony Britton) and his estranged wife, Angela (played by Dinah Sheridan\"/><figcaption>Britton starred alongside Dinah Sheridan in the BBC sitcom Don\'t Wait Up</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Actor and comedian Sanjeev Bhaskar paid tribute, writing: \"Profound condolences Fern and gratitude for the joy and entertainment your Dad brought to me and millions of others. Sending love and strength.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Actor Tony Britton has died aged 95, says daughter Fern','','publish','open','open','','actor-tony-britton-has-died-aged-95-says-daughter-fern','','','2019-12-24 05:47:32','2019-12-24 05:47:32','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=98',0,'post','',0),(99,1,'2019-12-24 05:47:32','2019-12-24 05:47:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A familiar face of classic British sitcoms, such as Robin\'s Nest, his film credits included The Day Of The Jackal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Don\'t Wait Up star Tony Britton has died aged 95, his TV presenter daughter Fern has announced.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Writing on Twitter, she hailed her father as a \"great actor, director and charmer\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Britton was best known for starring alongside Nigel Havers and Dinah Sheridan in the BBC sitcom Don\'t Wait Up between 1983 to 1990.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He also appeared in Thames Television\'s Robin\'s Nest, which aired from 1977 to 1981, together with Richard O\'Sullivan and Tessa Wyatt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>His film credits included The Day Of The Jackal, Operation Amsterdam and Sunday Bloody Sunday.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-tony-britton-dinah_4873512.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191222113324\" alt=\"Love is rekindled between Dr Toby Latimer (actor Tony Britton) and his estranged wife, Angela (played by Dinah Sheridan\"/><figcaption>Britton starred alongside Dinah Sheridan in the BBC sitcom Don\'t Wait Up</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Actor and comedian Sanjeev Bhaskar paid tribute, writing: \"Profound condolences Fern and gratitude for the joy and entertainment your Dad brought to me and millions of others. Sending love and strength.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Actor Tony Britton has died aged 95, says daughter Fern','','inherit','closed','closed','','98-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:47:32','2019-12-24 05:47:32','',98,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=99',0,'revision','',0),(100,1,'2019-12-24 05:49:36','2019-12-24 05:49:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hollywood star Jake Gyllenhaal is heading to the West End next summer to play French painter Georges Seurat.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllanhaal-celebrity_4868392.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191216183302\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal on why UK audiences are the best listeners in the world. \"/><figcaption>Why London audiences are the \'best listeners\'</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Jake Gyllenhaal has praised theatre audiences in the UK ahead of his return to the West End.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://news.sky.com/topic/jake-gyllenhaal-7331\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The Oscar-nominated US actor </strong></a>is bringing his sold-out Broadway show Sunday In The Park With George to the Savoy Theatre in June.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870818.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191219130200\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal as George and Annaleigh Ashford as Dot in Sunday in the Park with George on Broadway. Photographer credit: Matthew Murphy \"/><figcaption>Gyllenhaal and Annaleigh Ashford will both reprise their Broadway roles. Pic: Matthew Murphy</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s been 18 years since he last performed on the London stage, when he appeared in Kenneth Lonergan\'s play This Is Our Youth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal and American actress Annaleigh Ashford are both reprising their roles of a painter and his mistress in the musical by Stephen Sondheim and James Lapine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, Gyllenhaal believes it won\'t be the exact same show: \"To bring it here to the city I feel like is the bastion of theatre, and also to an audience that listens better than any audience in the world, will be a whole new experience,\" he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I remember the last show we did in New York we were looking at each other singing the last song and thinking this does not feel like the end, it\'s meant to go somewhere else, it\'s meant to be born somewhere else, and it\'s sort of being reborn here.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal went on to explain that he believes UK audiences are different to others he\'s performed for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I think there is a big difference, and I do think it comes down to listening,\" he explained.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Not to say that American audiences or audiences over the world don\'t listen, but it\'s a different kind of listening.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870817.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191219130157\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal as George in Sunday in the Park with George on Broadway. Photographer credit: Matthew Murphy \"/><figcaption>Gyllenhaal says true love is about making art with the people you\'re closest to. Pic: Matthew Murphy</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The actor had been on stage in London the night prior to the interview.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I could feel it even last night, we performed a little bit last night and I remember that feeling as a performer,\" Gyllenhaal said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"You can kind of feel that searing feeling of a listening mind, and I just adore it, I love it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"It leaves you with, I don\'t know, there\'s high expectations, which I like.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The musical is inspired by the French painter Georges Seurat and his famous work A Sunday Afternoon On The Island Of La Grande Jatte.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the piece the fictionalised artist is obsessed with finishing his masterpiece, and sings about it in the song Finishing The Hat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal said he believes the song is about fear of intimacy, and using work to avoid emotional connection is something he can relate to.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I think that so often with our work, no matter what it is that we do, I think we always revert to that,\" he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"It is a safer space, it\'s a space that may have intimacy in it, but ultimately doesn\'t involve all of the complexities of interacting with another human being and trying to be close and honest with them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"And I think this song is really about that and about how hard it is for these two people to get close, because there\'s always this other thing, this other love.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"And it is a true love - creating and making art or whatever it is that you do - but the real stuff is when you get into it with the people you\'re closest to.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sunday In The Park with George will be on at the Savoy Theatre from June 2020.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Jake Gyllenhaal: UK audiences are the best listeners in the world','','publish','open','open','','jake-gyllenhaal-uk-audiences-are-the-best-listeners-in-the-world','','','2019-12-24 05:49:36','2019-12-24 05:49:36','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=100',0,'post','',0),(101,1,'2019-12-24 05:49:36','2019-12-24 05:49:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hollywood star Jake Gyllenhaal is heading to the West End next summer to play French painter Georges Seurat.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllanhaal-celebrity_4868392.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191216183302\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal on why UK audiences are the best listeners in the world. \"/><figcaption>Why London audiences are the \'best listeners\'</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Jake Gyllenhaal has praised theatre audiences in the UK ahead of his return to the West End.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://news.sky.com/topic/jake-gyllenhaal-7331\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The Oscar-nominated US actor </strong></a>is bringing his sold-out Broadway show Sunday In The Park With George to the Savoy Theatre in June.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870818.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191219130200\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal as George and Annaleigh Ashford as Dot in Sunday in the Park with George on Broadway. Photographer credit: Matthew Murphy \"/><figcaption>Gyllenhaal and Annaleigh Ashford will both reprise their Broadway roles. Pic: Matthew Murphy</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s been 18 years since he last performed on the London stage, when he appeared in Kenneth Lonergan\'s play This Is Our Youth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal and American actress Annaleigh Ashford are both reprising their roles of a painter and his mistress in the musical by Stephen Sondheim and James Lapine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, Gyllenhaal believes it won\'t be the exact same show: \"To bring it here to the city I feel like is the bastion of theatre, and also to an audience that listens better than any audience in the world, will be a whole new experience,\" he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I remember the last show we did in New York we were looking at each other singing the last song and thinking this does not feel like the end, it\'s meant to go somewhere else, it\'s meant to be born somewhere else, and it\'s sort of being reborn here.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal went on to explain that he believes UK audiences are different to others he\'s performed for.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I think there is a big difference, and I do think it comes down to listening,\" he explained.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Not to say that American audiences or audiences over the world don\'t listen, but it\'s a different kind of listening.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://e3.365dm.com/19/12/768x432/skynews-jake-gyllenhaal-sunday-park-george_4870817.jpg?bypass-service-worker&amp;20191219130157\" alt=\"Jake Gyllenhaal as George in Sunday in the Park with George on Broadway. Photographer credit: Matthew Murphy \"/><figcaption>Gyllenhaal says true love is about making art with the people you\'re closest to. Pic: Matthew Murphy</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The actor had been on stage in London the night prior to the interview.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I could feel it even last night, we performed a little bit last night and I remember that feeling as a performer,\" Gyllenhaal said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"You can kind of feel that searing feeling of a listening mind, and I just adore it, I love it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"It leaves you with, I don\'t know, there\'s high expectations, which I like.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The musical is inspired by the French painter Georges Seurat and his famous work A Sunday Afternoon On The Island Of La Grande Jatte.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the piece the fictionalised artist is obsessed with finishing his masterpiece, and sings about it in the song Finishing The Hat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gyllenhaal said he believes the song is about fear of intimacy, and using work to avoid emotional connection is something he can relate to.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I think that so often with our work, no matter what it is that we do, I think we always revert to that,\" he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"It is a safer space, it\'s a space that may have intimacy in it, but ultimately doesn\'t involve all of the complexities of interacting with another human being and trying to be close and honest with them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"And I think this song is really about that and about how hard it is for these two people to get close, because there\'s always this other thing, this other love.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"And it is a true love - creating and making art or whatever it is that you do - but the real stuff is when you get into it with the people you\'re closest to.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sunday In The Park with George will be on at the Savoy Theatre from June 2020.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Jake Gyllenhaal: UK audiences are the best listeners in the world','','inherit','closed','closed','','100-revision-v1','','','2019-12-24 05:49:36','2019-12-24 05:49:36','',100,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=101',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2019-12-24 05:51:58','2019-12-24 05:51:58','<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap\">At 18.07 on the 23 December, I’ll be at London Liverpool Street station boarding the train to north Essex, where my parents live.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The next day, my husband David will jump on the 18.12 from London Waterloo to a dormitory town in Surrey, where he grew up. And we won’t see each other again until 28&nbsp;December when I’ll make the pilgrimage through London – during a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/travel/news-and-advice/south-western-railway-strike-trains-cancelled-rail-christmas-december-rmt-union-a9226746.html\">South Western Railway train strike</a>, no less&nbsp;– to his family home in Epsom.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So no, we’re not spending the season to be jolly together, just like we haven’t spent it together for the past 12 years – even though we’ve been married for almost four. Oh, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/women/pregnancy-body-changes-six-months-self-comments-a9220216.html\">I’m 28 weeks pregnant</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have begrudgingly spent a few Boxing Days together, which usually involve the most miserable three-word phrase that exists in the English language – rail replacement bus – or asking an ageing parent to drop us off at the nearest Tube station. Ho ho ho and three hours stuck in traffic on the M11!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We did spend Christmas together once: in Western Australia in 2016, the year we got married, aka the Christmas That Shall Not Be Named. I have since decided it doesn’t really count when the mercury is tipping 30 degrees and the only sign of Christmas is the garishly dressed Norwegian spruce in the hotel casino. I did it, more than anything, to prove to myself I could spend a Christmas outside of Essex and while we were living in Hong Kong (just an eight-hour flight away) it seemed like a good enough excuse. “Avoid the family drama!!!” I’d say loftily to people that were aghast I was spending my favourite day of the year on the other side of the world.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But then… I sobbed after Skyping my family, eight hours’ behind in the UK, who appeared to have forgotten my non-existence entirely. Why was I sat in a dim-lit, velour-covered hotel bar when I should be arguing with my dad about the thermostat? Who were all these people who choose to spend Christmas Day in a faceless hotel rather than with family – did people think we had nowhere else to go? (Things improved immeasurably on Boxing Day, where our “Christmas holiday in the sun” became just an ordinary boozy trip. Which is how it will stay in my memory.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That miserable experience of weeping into my whisky sour was not one to be repeated and the following year we voicelessly resumed our normal Christmas routine of going back to our respective family homes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The benefits: I get to spend Christmas Eve in the local Wetherspoon\'s (which until I was about 28 remained the Biggest Night Out of the whole year) and David gets to get boozed up with his school friends in the confusingly named Leg of Mutton and Cauliflower pub. We wake up hungover in our childhood bedrooms and don’t have to make excuses to our in-laws when we spend the morning driving the porcelain bus.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Plus, I’m stubborn and refuse to desert the Christmas traditions I’ve had with my family for 33 years. Everybody thinks they do Christmas best, but… sorry, we actually do. I couldn’t imagine swapping the annual frosty morning walk and game of Cluedo for sitting doing God-knows-what with my husband’s family. Although he did say that last year my brother- and sister-in-law cooked a Christmas buffet from scratch, including a dessert&nbsp;<em>table</em>, which almost made me reconsider.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Besides, my family have better stories. One year my brother got so drunk on Christmas Eve he tucked into the chicken casserole that had been left on the stove ready for Christmas Day (yeah, we don’t always have a proper dinner either). My mum first became suspicious when she found a chicken gravy handprint on his door, followed by the sight of her son legging it up the stairs, trailed by chicken bits. Our Christmas dinner was chicken casserole sauce on toast, the only thing salvageable from the pilfered royal blue Le Creuset. Which explained why, when my sister and I returned squiffy from the pub later on Christmas Eve, we found it wrapped up with angry spools of parcel tape around it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Of course, David is always welcome to spend Christmas with my family, but to nobody’s surprise but my own he has always opted not to.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By next Christmas, we’ll have a baby son, which I&nbsp;<em>think</em>&nbsp;might mean we have to spend at least part of “the Day” together. At 33 it’s probably time to accept that my family will have evolved from me being the eldest, most difficult sibling in a family of five to being a parent myself. It’ll mean no more Christmas Eve pub visits, no drunken chicken casserole anecdotes and no blathering about who&nbsp;<em>really</em>&nbsp;wants to watch the Queen’s Speech. I’m hoping it’ll still be just as magical… but in an entirely different way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','I’ve been with my husband for 12 years and we never spend Christmas together','','publish','open','open','','ive-been-with-my-husband-for-12-years-and-we-never-spend-christmas-together','','','2019-12-24 05:51:58','2019-12-24 05:51:58','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=102',0,'post','',0),(103,1,'2019-12-24 05:50:52','2019-12-24 05:50:52','','christmas-0','','inherit','open','closed','','christmas-0','','','2019-12-24 05:50:52','2019-12-24 05:50:52','',102,'http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/christmas-0.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(104,1,'2019-12-24 05:51:58','2019-12-24 05:51:58